We got into our room and was pleasantly surprised that although it was small, there was a small kitchen, living room and separate bedroom.	The suites are well equipped with a fully functional kitchen, even though the bedroom it self is a bit small.	The suite gave us a great view over Stanley Park, the city and the water and the room was clean, compact and bijou.	The suite we were initially given was on the 6th floor and was very noisy as you could hear the air conditioning from the ground outside.	Room itself had a separate sitting room / kitchen but the decor is a bit dated and probably in need of a revamp.